Verses.Text:
 ‘But cross over to the coastlands of the Kitʹtim and see.
Yes, send to Keʹdar and consider carefully;
See whether anything like this has happened.

 Even your skirts are stained with the blood of the innocent poor ones,
Though I did not find them in the act of breaking in;
It is on all your skirts.

 For this reason also you will go out with your hands on your head,
For Jehovah has rejected those in whom you put confidence;
They will not bring you success.”

 “In that day,” declares Jehovah, “the heart of the king will fail him,
Also the heart of the princes;
The priests will be horrified, and the prophets will be amazed.”

 “Hear this, you foolish and senseless people:
They have eyes but cannot see;
They have ears but cannot hear.

 They have grown fat and smooth;
They overflow with evil.
They do not plead the legal case of the fatherless,
That they may gain success;
And they deny justice to the poor.’”

 “I have made you a metal tester among my people,
One making a thorough search;
You must take note and examine their way.

 Why is this people, Jerusalem, unfaithful with an enduring unfaithfulness?
They hold fast to deception;
They refuse to turn back.

 Even the stork in the sky knows its seasons;
The turtledove and the swift and the thrush keep to the time of their return.
But my own people do not understand the judgment of Jehovah.”’

 So I will give their wives to other men,
Their fields to other owners;
For from the least to the greatest, each one is making dishonest gain;
From the prophet to the priest, each one is practicing fraud.

 I am shattered over the breakdown of the daughter of my people;
I am dejected.
Horror has seized me.

 This is what Jehovah says:
“Let not the wise man boast about his wisdom;
Let not the mighty man boast about his mightiness;
And let not the rich man boast about his riches.”

 Who should not fear you, O King of the nations, for it is fitting;
Because among all the wise ones of the nations and among all their kingdoms,
There is no one at all like you.

 Many shepherds have destroyed my vineyard;
They have trampled my portion of land.
They have turned my desirable portion of land into a desolate wilderness.

 The wild donkeys stand on the bare hills.
They pant for air like jackals;
Their eyes fail because there is no vegetation.

 For the sake of your name, do not reject us;
Do not despise your glorious throne.
Remember, and do not break your covenant with us.

 Jehovah said: “I will surely minister to you for good;
I will surely intercede for you in the time of calamity,
In the time of distress against the enemy.

 Your words were found, and I ate them;
And your word became to me the exultation and the rejoicing of my heart,
For your name has been called on me, O Jehovah God of armies.

 This is what Jehovah says:
“We have heard the sounds of trembling;
There is terror, and no peace.

 For a nation has come against her from the north.
It makes her land an object of horror;
No one is dwelling in her.
Both man and beast have taken flight;
They have gone away.”

 Look! A people is coming in from the north;
A great nation and grand kings will be raised up
From the remotest parts of the earth.

 I will send winnowers to Babylon,
And they will winnow her and make her land empty;
They will come against her on all sides in the day of calamity.

 Babylon has been a golden cup in the hand of Jehovah;
She made all the earth drunk.
From her wine the nations have drunk;
That is why the nations have gone mad.

 “King Nebuchadnezʹzar of Babylon has devoured me;
He has thrown me into confusion.
He has set me down as an empty vessel.
He has swallowed me down like a big snake;
He has filled his stomach with my fine things.
He has rinsed me away.
